            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1612195695365-x200.jpg",
