            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1612195699583-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger paste</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and<strong> curry powder</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>coconut stock </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 5-6 min further or until thickened – this is your <strong>korma sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
